menu "espAGC PROG ALARM watchdog"

config AGC_AUTO_RSET_AT_BOOT
    bool "Send a synthetic RSET ~1.5 s after boot to flush PROG ALARM"
    default y
    help
        Posts one DSKY_KEY_RSET keycode to channel 015 once the engine
        has run ~16 ChannelRoutine ticks (about 1.5 s wall-time). Used
        together with the peripheral_stub watchdog to keep the PROG
        ALARM lamp clear at idle. Disable to observe raw alarm
        behavior for debugging the underlying peripheral state.

config AGC_TRACE_KEYRUPT1
    bool "Trace KEYRUPT1 / NOVAC execution to UART"
    default n
    help
        Enable per-instruction UART logging while the engine is
        executing inside the KEYRUPT1 fixed-fixed window
        (RegZ in 04024..04046). Captures FBANK/BBANK/A/L/Q plus
        the two words at the address in Q (NOVAC's DCA target).
        Diagnostic for the keypress-dispatch bug documented in
        docs/NEXT_SESSION.md: on hardware, NOVAC schedules CHARIN
        with a bad CADR (077615). With this flag on, the trace
        will show whether the engine reads the correct 2CADR
        words at the moment of DCA. Leave off in production -
        emits ~16 log lines per keypress.

endmenu
